---
description: agentic-setup project conventions for TypeScript CLI development
alwaysApply: true
---
- ESM imports require `.js` extensions.
- `unknown` over `any` — ESLint warns on explicit any.
- Tests mirror `src/` layout, global setup in `tests/setup.ts`.
- Run tests: `npm run test` or `npx vitest run tests/scoring/accuracy.test.ts`.
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`.